msgstr "Apple Mobile: Alternative al ligam de l’aplicacion iOS"

msgid "Mobile: Mobile Optimized"
msgstr "Mobile: Optimizat per mòbil"

msgid "Mobile: Theme Color"
msgstr "Mobile: Color del tèma"

msgid "Mobile: Viewport"
msgstr "Mòbil : Finestra de visualizacion"

msgid ""
"A custom string for deeplinking to an Android mobile app. Should be in "
"the format 'package_name/host_path', e.g. "
"'com.example.android/example/hello-screen'. The 'android-app://' "
"prefix will be included automatically."
msgstr ""
"Una cadena personalizada per a l'enllaç profund cap a una aplidacion "
"mòbila Android. Deuriá èsser dins lo format "
"'package_name/host_path', per exemple "
"'com.example.android/example/hello-screen'. Lo prefixe "
"'android-app://' serà integrat automaticament."

msgid ""
"This informs iOS devices to display a banner to a specific app. If "
"used, it must provide the 'app-id' value, the 'affiliate-data' and "
"'app-argument' values are optional."
msgstr ""
"Aquel mensaje indica als aparelhs iOS d'afichar una banniera per una "
"aplicacion specifica. Se s'utiliza, cal fornir la valor 'app-id', los "
"valors 'affiliate-data' e 'app-argument' son opcionals."

msgid ""
"If set to 'yes', the application will run in full-screen mode; the "
"default behavior is to use Safari to display web content."
msgstr ""
"Se definat a « oui », l'aplicacion foncionarà en mòde de talha "
"completa ; lo comportament per defòrt es d'utilizar Safari per "
"afichar lo contengut web."

msgid ""
"Requires the 'Web app capable' meta tag to be set to 'yes'. May be set "
"to 'default', 'black', or 'black-translucent'."
msgstr ""
"Requèr la meta etiqueta « Web app capable » configurada a « yes "
"». pòt èsser configurada a « default », « black », o « "
"black-translucent »."

msgid ""
"A legacy meta tag for older versions of Internet Explorer on Windows, "
"use the value 'on' to enable it; this tag is ignored by all other "
"browsers."
msgstr ""
"Una meta etiqueta antiga per las ancianas versions d’Internet "
"Explorer sus Windows, utilizatz la valor 'on' per l’activar; aquesta "
"etiqueta es ignorada per totes las autras navegadors."

msgid ""
"If set to 'telephone=no' the page will not be checked for phone "
"numbers, which would be presented."
msgstr ""
"Se es definit a 'telephone=no' la pagina serà pas verificada per "
"numeros de telefòn, que serián pas presentan."

msgid ""
"Some older mobile browsers will expect this meta tag to be set to "
"'true' to indicate that the site has been designed with mobile "
"browsers in mind."
msgstr ""
"Quauques navegadors mobilièrs mai vièlhs s’esperan que aquesta "
"meta tag siá fixada a 'true' per indicar que lo sitèis a estat "
"concebut en pensant als navegadors mobilièrs."

msgid ""
"A custom string for deeplinking to an iOS mobile app. Should be in the "
"format 'itunes_id/scheme/host_path', e.g. "
"123456/example/hello-screen'. The 'ios-app://' prefix will be included "
"automatically."
msgstr ""
"Una cadena personalizaa per lo deeplinking cap a una aplicacion mòbil "
"iOS. Dobrís èsser dins lo format 'itunes_id/scheme/host_path', per "
"exemple 123456/example/hello-screen'. Lo prèfixe 'ios-app://' serà "
"includit automaticament."

msgid ""
"Using the value 'width' tells certain mobile Internet Explorer "
"browsers to display as-is, without being resized. Alternatively a "
"numerical width may be used to indicate the desired page width the "
"page should be rendered in: '240' is the suggested default, '176' for "
"older browsers or '480' for newer devices with high DPI screens."
msgstr ""
"Utilizar la valor 'width' indica a qualques navegadors Internet "
"Explorer mobil de mostrar tal qual, sens èsser redimensionats. "
"Alternativament, se pòt utilizar una largor numerica per indicar la "
"largor de pagina desirada ont la pagina deurà èsser renduda: '240' "
"es lo defaut suggerit, '176' pels navegadors mai vièlhs o '480' pels "
"aparelhs mai novèls amb d’escans d’auta resolucion (DPI)."

msgid ""
"Allows tasks to be defined on child domains of the fully qualified "
"domain name associated with the pinned site. Should be either 'true' "
"or 'false'."
msgstr ""
"Permet de definir de tasques sus de domenis fieus del nom de domeni "
"complet asociat amb lo site fixat. Deuriá èsser 'true' o 'false'."

msgid ""
"Should contain the full URL to a <a "
"href='https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/dn320426(v=vs.85).aspx'>Browser "
"configuration schema</a> file that further controls tile "
"customizations."
msgstr ""
"Deuriá contenir l’URL completa d’un fichièr <a "
"href='https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/dn320426(v=vs.85).aspx'>d’esquema "
"de configuracion del navegador</a> que controla mai las "
"personalizacions de las tièlas."

msgid ""
"A semi-colon -separated string containing 'polling-uri=' (required), "
"'polling-uri2=', 'polling-uri3=', 'polling-uri4=' and 'polling-uri5=' "
"to indicate the URLs for notifications. May also contain a "
"'frequency=' value to specify how often (in minutes) the URLs will be "
"polled; limited to 30, 60, 360, 720 or 1440 (default). May also "
"contain the value 'cycle=' to control the notifications cycle."
msgstr ""
"Una cadena separada per un punt e virgula que conten 'polling-uri=' "
"(obligatòri), 'polling-uri2=', 'polling-uri3=', 'polling-uri4=' e "
"'polling-uri5=' per indicar las URL per las notificacions. Pòt tanben "
"conténer una valor 'frequency=' per precisar la frequéncia (en "
"minutas) a la quala las URL seràn sondadas; limitada a 30, 60, 360, "
"720 o 1440 (per defaut). Pòt tanben conténer la valor 'cycle=' per "
"contrar lo cicle de las notificacions."

msgid ""
"A semi-colon -separated string defining the 'jump' list task. Should "
"contain the 'name=' value to specify the task's name, the "
"'action-uri=' value to set the URL to load when the jump list is "
"clicked, the 'icon-uri=' value to set the URL to an icon file to be "
"displayed, and 'window-type=' set to either 'tab' (default), 'self' or "
"'window' to control how the link opens in the browser."
msgstr ""
"Una cadena separada per un punt e virgula que definís la tasca de la "
"lista de «salt». Deu contener la valor «name=» per especificar lo "
"nom de la tasca, la valor «action-uri=» per indicar l'URL a cargar "
"quand se clic en la lista de salt, la valor «icon-uri=» per indicar "
"l'URL d'un fichièr d'icon que serà afichat, e «window-type=» "
"ajustat a «tab» (per defaut), «self» o «window» per controlar "
"cossí lo ligam s'obrís dins lo navigador."

msgid ""
"A semi-colon -separated value that controls the dimensions of the "
"initial window. Should contain the values 'width=' and 'height=' to "
"control the width and height respectively."
msgstr ""
"Una valor separada per un punt e virgula que controla las dimensionas "
"de la fenèstra iniciala. Deuriá conténer las valors 'width=' e "
"'height=' per controlar la largessa e l'autessa respectivament."

msgid "Metatag: Open Graph Products"
msgstr "Metatag : Produches Open Graph"

msgid ""
"In the context of search engine optimization, providing an extensive "
"set of meta tags may help improve the site's and pages' rankings, thus "
"may aid with achieving a more prominent display of the content within "
"search engine results. They can also be used to tailor how content is "
"displayed when shared on social networks. For additional information, "
"see the <a href=\":online\">online documentation for Metatag</a>."
msgstr ""
"Dins lo contèxt de l'optimizacion per motors de recèrca, provesir un "
"enjoveniment ample de balises meta pòt ajudar a melhorar lo "
"rangiament del siti e de las paginas, çò que pòt apondre a obténer "
"una presentacion mai importanta del contengut dins los resultats dels "
"motors de recèrca. Pòt tanben èsser utilizat per adaptar lo biais "
"que se mostra lo contengut quand es partejat sus las retas socialas. "
"Per mai d'informacions, vei la <a href=\":online\">documentacion en "
"linha per Metatag</a>."

msgid ""
"Override each of the <a href=\":defaults\">other defaults</a>, fill in "
"specific values and tokens that each item should have by default. This "
"allows e.g. for all nodes to have different values than taxonomy "
"terms."
msgstr ""
"Substituïtz cadun dels <a href=\":defaults\">auts valors per "
"defaut</a>, emplenatz de valors especifics e tokens que cadun "
"d'aqueles elements deu aver per defaut. Aquò permet per exemple que "
"totas las nòdas agan de valors diferents dels tèrmes de taxonomia."

msgid ""
"These meta tags are designed to point visitors to versions of the "
"current page in other languages."
msgstr ""
"Aquelas meta tèxtes son concebuts per dirigir los visitaires cap a de "
"versions de la pagina actuala dins d’autras lengas."

msgid "Sitename"
msgstr "Nom del siti"

msgid ""
"Meta tag patterns are passed down from one level to the next unless "
"they are overridden. To view a summary of the individual meta tags and "
"the pattern for a specific configuration, click on its name below."
msgstr ""
"Los patrons de balises meta se transmeton d’un nivèl a l’autre a "
"mens que sián remplaçats. Per veure un resum de las balises meta "
"individualas e lo patron per una configuracion especifica, clicatz sus "
"son nom aicí jos."

msgid ""
"The URL of an video which should represent the content. For best "
"results use a source that is at least 1200 x 630 pixels in size, but "
"at least 600 x 316 pixels is a recommended minimum. Object types "
"supported include video.episode, video.movie, video.other, and "
"video.tv_show."
msgstr ""
"L'URL d'un vidèo que deu representar lo contengut. Per de melhors "
"resultats, utilizatz una sorga que siá almens de 1200 x 630 pixels de "
"talha, mas almens 600 x 316 pixels es una talha minima recomanada. Los "
"types d'objèctes acceptats includisson video.episode, video.movie, "
"video.other, e video.tv_show."

msgid ""
"The type of video referenced above. Should be either  video.episode, "
"video.movie, video.other, and video.tv_show. Note: there should be one "
"value for each video, and having more than there are videos may cause "
"problems."
msgstr ""
"Lo tipe de vidèo indicat sus lo dessenhat. Deuriá èsser o ben "
"video.episode, video.movie, video.other, o video.tv_show. Nota: i "
"deurà aver una sola valor per cada vidèo, e nebotar mai de valors "
"que lo nombre de vidèos pòt provocar de problèmas."

msgid "Provides views integration for metatags."
msgstr "Proporciona una integracion de vistas per metatags."

msgid "Metatags for @view : @display have been saved."
msgstr "Metatags per @view : @display an estat enregistrats."

msgid "Edit @language translation for %view: %display metatags"
msgstr "Modificar la traduccion en @language per %view: %display metataques"

msgid "Metatag display extender"
msgstr "Extendentor d'afichatge de Metatag"

msgid "Metatag settings for this view."
msgstr "Configuracions de metatags per aquesta vista."

msgid ""
"A link to the preferred page location or URL of the content of this "
"page, to help eliminate duplicate content penalties from search "
"engines."
msgstr ""
"Un ligam cap a la posicion preferida de la pagina o l’URL del "
"contengut d’aquesta pagina, per ajudar a eliminar las penalitats de "
"contengut duplitjat pels motors de recèrca."

msgid ""
"The text to display in the title bar of a visitor's web browser when "
"they view this page. This meta tag may also be used as the title of "
"the page when a visitor bookmarks or favorites this page, or as the "
"page title in a search engine result. It is common to append "
"'[site:name]' to the end of this, so the site's name is automatically "
"added. It is recommended that the title is no greater than 55 - 65 "
"characters long, including spaces."
msgstr ""
"Lo tèxte per afichar dins la barra del títol del navigador web "
"d’un visitator quand consulta aquesta pagina. Aquesta etiqueta meta "
"pòt tanben èsser utilizada coma títol de la pagina quand un "
"visitator marca o fava la pagina dins sos favorits, o coma títol de "
"la pagina dins los resultats d’un motòr de recèrca. Es corrent "
"d’ajustar '[site:name]' a la fin d’aquel tèxte, per que lo nom "
"del site siá apondut automaticament. Es recomandat que lo títol siá "
"pas mai long de 55 a 65 caractèrs, espaciats inclus."

msgid "URL for a version of this page in %langcode"
msgstr "Adreça URL per una version d'aquesta pagina en %langcode"

msgid "Hreflang per language"
msgstr "Hreflang per lenga"

msgid ""
"<a href='https://www.metatags.org/meta_http_equiv_set_cookie'>Sets a "
"cookie</a> on the visitor's browser. Can be in either NAME=VALUE "
"format, or a more verbose format including the path and expiration "
"date; see the link for full details on the syntax."
msgstr ""
"<a href='https://www.metatags.org/meta_http_equiv_set_cookie'>Met un "
"cookie</a> dins lo navegador del visitant. Ben pòt èsser en formato "
"NAME=VALUE, o un formato mai explicatiu que compren lo camin e la data "
"d’expiracion ; vesètz lo ligam per mai de detalhs sus la sintaxi."

msgid "Enables metatags for custom routes"
msgstr "Activa los metatags per las rotas personalizadas"

msgid "Add meta tag for custom route"
msgstr "Apondre una balisa meta per un trajècte personalizat"

msgid "Add custom metatag"
msgstr "Apondre una metatag personalizada"

msgid "The path must begin with /"
msgstr "Lo camin deu començar per /"

msgid "The admin routes should not have metatags."
msgstr "Las rotas d’administracion devon pas aver de metatags."

msgid "There are already metatags created for this route."
msgstr "I a ja de metatags creats per aquesta rota."

msgid "The path does not exist as an internal Drupal route."
msgstr "Lo camin existís pas coma un camin intern de Drupal."

msgid "Created metatags for the path: @url. Internal route: @route."
msgstr "Metatgèrs creats per lo camin : @url. Tracet intern : @route."

msgid "The metatags could not be created for the path: @url."
msgstr "Las metatags an pas pogut èsser creatas per lo camin: @url."

msgid "Dublin Core: Instructional Method"
msgstr "Dublin Core: Metòde Instructorial"

msgid "Dublin Core: Is Format Of"
msgstr "Dublin Core: Es un format de"

msgid "Dublin Core: Is Part Of"
msgstr "Dublin Core: Es Partit De"

msgid "Dublin Core: Is Referenced By"
msgstr "Dublin Core: Es Referenciat per"

msgid ""
"Information about who can access the resource or an indication of its "
"security status. Access Rights may include information regarding "
"access or restrictions based on privacy, security, or other policies."
msgstr ""
"Informacions sus quí pòt accedir a la ressorsa o una indicacion de "
"son estat de seguretat. Los dreches d’accès pòdon inclure "
"d’informacions concernent l’accès o las restriccions basadas sus "
"la privacitat, la seguretat, o d’autras politicas."

msgid ""
"A bibliographic reference for the resource. Recommended practice is to "
"include sufficient bibliographic detail to identify the resource as "
"unambiguously as possible."
msgstr ""
"Una referéncia bibliografic per la ressorsa. La practica recomandada "
"es d’enviar d’informacions bibliograficas a bastança per "
"identificar la ressorsa sens ambiguitat possible."

msgid ""
"Date of acceptance of the resource. Examples of resources to which a "
"Date Accepted may be relevant are a thesis (accepted by a university "
"department) or an article (accepted by a journal)."
msgstr ""
"Data d'acceptacion de la ressorsa. Exemples de ressorsas per las "
"qualas una Data Acceptada pòt èsser pertinent es una tèssi "
"(acceptada per un departament universitàri) o un article (acceptat "
"per una revista)."

msgid ""
"Date of submission of the resource. Examples of resources to which a "
"Date Submitted may be relevant are a thesis (submitted to a university "
"department) or an article (submitted to a journal)."
msgstr ""
"Data de sosmission de la ressorsa. D'exemples de ressorsas per las "
"qualas una Data de Sosmission poiriá èsser pertinent es una tèsi "
"(sosmesa a un departament universitàri) o un article (sosmés a una "
"revista)."

msgid ""
"A process, used to engender knowledge, attitudes and skills, that the "
"described resource is designed to support. Instructional Method will "
"typically include ways of presenting instructional materials or "
"conducting instructional activities, patterns of learner-to-learner "
"and learner-to-instructor interactions, and mechanisms by which group "
"and individual levels of learning are measured. Instructional methods "
"include all aspects of the instruction and learning processes from "
"planning and implementation through evaluation and feedback."
msgstr ""
"Un procèssus, utilizat per generar de coneissenças, d’atituds e de "
"competéncias, que la ressorsa descricha es conceputa per sosténer. "
"Lo Mètode Didactic va generalament inclure las manièras de presentar "
"los materials d’instruccion o de menar d’activitats didacticas, "
"los modèls d’interaccion entre aprenents e entre aprenent e "
"professor, e los mechanisms pels quals los nivèls d’aprendissatge "
"tant en grope coma individual son mesurats. Los metòdes didactics "
"comprenon totas las aspèctes del procèssus d’instruccion e "
"d’aprendissatge dempuèi la preparacion e la realizacion fins a "
"l’èvaluacion e lo retorn d’informacions."

msgid ""
"A related resource of which the described resource is a version, "
"edition, or adaptation. Changes in version imply substantive changes "
"in content rather than differences in format."
msgstr ""
"Una ressorsa relacionada de la qual la ressorsa descricha es una "
"version, una edicion o una adaptacion. Los cambiaments dins la version "
"implican de cambiaments substancials dins lo contengut puslèu que de "
"diferéncias de format."

msgid ""
"An entity that mediates access to the resource and for whom the "
"resource is intended or useful. In an educational context, a mediator "
"might be a parent, teacher, teaching assistant, or care-giver."
msgstr ""
"Una entitat que media l'accès a la ressorsa e per la quala la "
"ressorsa es destinada o utila. Dins un contèxt educatiu, un mediator "
"pòt èsser un paire, un professor, un assistent de çò que "
"s'ensenha, o un cuidador."

msgid ""
"A statement of any changes in ownership and custody of the resource "
"since its creation that are significant for its authenticity, "
"integrity, and interpretation. The statement may include a description "
"of any changes successive custodians made to the resource."
msgstr ""
"Una declaracion de quinaques changements dins la proprietat e la "
"custòdia de la ressorsa dempuèi sa creacion que sián importants per "
"son autenticitat, integritat e interpretacion. La declaracion pòt "
"incluir una descripcion de quinaques changements realizats per los "
"custòdis successius sus la ressorsa."

msgid "Spatial Coverage"
msgstr "Cobertura Espacial"

msgid ""
"Links a book to an author's Facebook profile, should be either URLs to "
"the author's profile page or their Facebook profile IDs."
msgstr ""
"Ligams un libre al perfil Facebook d'un autor, deurian èsser o ben "
"d'URLs a la pagina de profil de l'autor o los identifiants de son "
"perfil Facebook."

msgid ""
"The URL of an image which should represent the content. The image must "
"be at least 200 x 200 pixels in size; 600 x 316 pixels is a "
"recommended minimum size, and for best results use an image least 1200 "
"x 630 pixels in size. Supports PNG, JPEG and GIF formats. Should not "
"be used if og:image:url is used. Note: if multiple images are added "
"many services (e.g. Facebook) will default to the largest image, not "
"specifically the first one."
msgstr ""
"L'URL d'una imatge que deu representar lo contengut. L'imatge deu aver "
"almens 200 x 200 pixels; 600 x 316 pixels es una talha minima "
"recomandada, e per de resultats melhora utilisatz una imatge d'almens "
"1200 x 630 pixels de talha. Sosten los formats PNG, JPEG e GIF. "
"Deuriá pas èsser utilizat se og:image:url es utilizat. Nota : se "
"mantunas imatges son apondudas, fòrça servicis (per exemple "
"Facebook) utilizaràn per defaut l'imatge la mai granda, pas "
"necessàriament la primièra."

msgid "Open Graph Product: Price amount"
msgstr "Open Graph Producte : Quantitat del prètz"

msgid "Open Graph Product: Price currency"
msgstr "Open Graph Producte: Moneda del prètz"

msgid "Metatag: Pinterest"
msgstr "Metatga: Pinterest"

msgid "Provides support for Pinterest's custom meta tags."
msgstr "Provesís de supòrt pels meta tics personalizats de Pinterest."

msgid "Pinterest: Description"
msgstr "Pinterest: Description"

msgid "Pinterest: ID"
msgstr "Pinterest: ID"

msgid "Pinterest: Media"
msgstr "Pinterest: Medias"

msgid "Pinterest: No hover"
msgstr "Pinterest : Pas de survol"

msgid "Pinterest: No pin"
msgstr "Pinterest: Pas de pin"

msgid "Pinterest: URL"
msgstr "Pinterest: URL"

msgid ""
"A set of meta tags used to control how the site's content is consumed "
"by <a href='https://pinterest.com/'>Pinterest</a>."
msgstr ""
"Un ensemble de balises meta utilizadas per contrarotlar cossí lo "
"contengut del sit web es consumit per <a "
"href='https://pinterest.com/'>Pinterest</a>."

msgid "The Canonical Pinterest object to pin."
msgstr "L'objècte Canonical de Pinterest a epinglar."

msgid "The URL of media which should represent the content."
msgstr "L'URL del mèdia que deu representar lo contengut."

msgid ""
"Do not show hovering Save or Search buttons, generated by the "
"Pinterest browser extensions."
msgstr ""
"Non mòstrar los botons Save o Search que apareisson a l'afluqui, "
"generats pels extensions del navegador Pinterest."

msgid "No pin"
msgstr "Pas de pegat"

msgid ""
"Do not pin anything from this page. When selected, this option will "
"take precedence over all options below."
msgstr ""
"N'anclatz res d'aquesta pagina. Quand es seleccionada, aquela opcion "
"aurà prioritat sus totas las opcions jos aquestas."

msgid "Do not allow Pinterest visual search to happen from this page."
msgstr ""
"Non permetètz que la recèrca visuala de Pinterest aja d'aquesta "
"pagina."

msgid "The URL which should represent the content."
msgstr "L'URL que deu representar lo contengut."

msgid ""
"The custom admin pages for managing Views meta tags at "
"/admin/config/search/metatag/views have been disabled for now, "
"hopefully they'll be back in a future release. Until then, the meta "
"tags can be managed directly on each individual view via the \"Meta "
"tags\" section."
msgstr ""
"Las paginas d’administracion customizadas per gerir los meta-tags de "
"las Vistas a l’adreça /admin/config/search/metatag/views son "
"desactivadas per ara, espèri que tornaràn dins una version venenta. "
"Fins a aquela fecha, los meta-tags se pòdon gerir directament sus "
"cada vista individuala al biais de la seccion « Meta tags »."

msgid ""
"To view a list of displays with meta tags set up, click on a view "
"name. To view a summary of meta tags configuration for a particular "
"display, click on the display name. If you need to set meta tags for a "
"specific view, choose Add views meta tags. Reverting the meta tags "
"removes the specific configuration and falls back to defaults."
msgstr ""
"Per veire una lista d'afichatges amb metatèxtes configurats, clicatz "
"sus un nom de vista. Per veire un resum de la configuracion dels "
"metatèxtes per un afichatge particular, clicatz sus lo nom de "
"l'afichatge. Se cal configurar metatèxtes per una vista especifica, "
"causissètz Apondre metatèxtes de vistas. Tornar als metatèxtes "
"elimina la configuracion especifica e torna a las valors per defaut."

msgid "Do you want to revert meta tags for @view_name : @display_name?"
msgstr "Volètz revertir los meta-tags per @view_name : @display_name ?"

msgid ""
"You are about to revert the custom meta tags for the %display_name "
"display on the %view_name view. This action cannot be undone."
msgstr ""
"Sètz a punt de revertir las mètas personalizadas per l'afichatge "
"%display_name sus la vista %view_name. Aquesta accion es pas "
"reversible."

msgid "Reverted meta tags for @view_name : @display_name"
msgstr "Metatags revertits per @view_name : @display_name"

msgid "Mobile: Web Manifest"
msgstr "Mobil: Manifest web"

msgid "Web Manifest"
msgstr "Manifest web"

msgid "Image 'alt'"
msgstr "Image 'alt'"

msgid ""
"A description of what is in the image, not a caption. If the page "
"specifies an og:image it should specify og:image:alt."
msgstr ""
"Una descripcion del contengut de l'imatge, pas una legenda. Se la "
"pagina especifica un og:image, deu tanben especificar og:image:alt."

msgid "Provides metatag support for Page Manager variants."
msgstr ""
"Provesís compatibilitat amb metatags pels variants del Gestor de "
"paginas."

msgid ""
"Identify which metatag groups should be available on which entity type "
"/ bundle combination. Unselected groups will not appear on the "
"configuration form for that entity type, reducing the size of the form "
"and increasing performance. If no groups are selected for a type, all "
"groups will appear."
msgstr ""
"Identificatz quines gropes de metatags deuràn èsser disponibles sus "
"quina combinason de tipe d'entitat / paquet. Los grops no seleccionats "
"apareisson pas sul formulari de configuracion per aqueste tipe "
"d'entitat, reduissent la talha del formulari e aumentant las "
"performanças. Se cap de grop es seleccionat per un tipe, totes los "
"grops apareisson."

msgid ""
"This meta tag communicates with Google. There are currently two "
"directives supported: 'nositelinkssearchbox' to not to show the "
"sitelinks search box, and 'notranslate' to ask Google not to offer a "
"translation of the page. Both options may be added, just separate them "
"with a comma. See <a "
"href='https://support.google.com/webmasters/answer/79812?hl=en'>meta "
"tags that Google understands</a> for further details."
msgstr ""
"Aquesta meta etiqueta comunica amb Google. Actualament, doas "
"directivas son acceptadas : 'nositelinkssearchbox' per pas mostrar la "
"trapa de recèrca dels ligams del site, e 'notranslate' per demandar a "
"Google de pas prepausar una traduccion de la pagina. Amb doas opcions "
"pòdon èsser apondudas, basta de las separar amb una virgula. Vejatz "
"<a "
"href='https://support.google.com/webmasters/answer/79812?hl=en'>meta "
"tags que Google compren</a> per mai de detalhs."

msgid "SVG icon"
msgstr "icòna SVG"

msgid "Pocket"
msgstr "Pòca"

msgid ""
"Warning: disabling the Global default metatag will prevent any "
"metatags from being used."
msgstr ""
"Atencion : desactivar lo metatag global per defaut empacharà "
"l’utilizacion de quina que siá metatag."

msgid ""
"Set the maximum size of an image preview for this page in a search "
"results."
msgstr ""
"Definissètz la talha màxima d'una previsualizacion d'imatge per "
"aquesta pagina dins los resultats de recèrca."

msgid "Standard - a default image preview may be shown."
msgstr "Estandard - se pòt afichar un apercebut d’imatge per defecte."

msgid ""
"Large - a larger image preview, up to the width of the viewport, may "
"be shown."
msgstr ""
"Grand - pòt èsser mostrada una previsualizacion d'imatge mai granda, "
"fins a la largor de la vitrina."

msgid "Metatag: Favicons"
msgstr "Metatag: Favicons"

msgid ""
"Provides an absolute URL to a specially formatted version of the "
"current page designed for 'feature phones', mobile phones that do not "
"support modern browser standards. See the <a "
"href='https://developers.google.com/webmasters/mobile-sites/mobile-seo/other-devices?hl=en#feature_phones'>official "
"Google Mobile SEO Guide</a> for details on how the page should be "
"formatted."
msgstr ""
"Proporciona una URL absoluta cap a una version formatada d'una "
"manièra especifica de la pagina corenta destinada als «feature "
"phones», telefòns mobiles que sostèngon pas los estandards "
"modèrnes dels navigadors. Vejatz lo <a "
"href='https://developers.google.com/webmasters/mobile-sites/mobile-seo/other-devices?hl=en#feature_phones'>gudari "
"oficiau de Google Mobile SEO</a> per detalhs sus cossí la pagina deu "
"èsser formatada."

msgid "Open Graph: Video duration"
msgstr "Open Graph : Durada del vidèo"

msgid ""
"The date this content will expire, with an optional time value. Needs "
"to be in <a href='https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601'>ISO 8601</a> "
"format."
msgstr ""
"La data d'expiracion d'aqueste contengut, amb una valor de temps "
"opcionau. Deu èsser en fòrm <a "
"href='https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601'>ISO 8601</a>."

msgid ""
"The date this content was last modified, with an optional time value. "
"Needs to be in <a href='https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601'>ISO "
"8601</a> format."
msgstr ""
"La data ont aqueste contengut foguèt modificat per la darrièra còp, "
"amb un valor de temps opcional. Devís èsser en format <a "
"href='https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601'>ISO 8601</a>."

msgid ""
"The date this content was published on, with an optional time value. "
"Needs to be in <a href='https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601'>ISO "
"8601</a> format."
msgstr ""
"La data a la quala aqueste contengut foguèt publicat, amb una ora "
"opcionalsa. De besonh qu’es en <a "
"href='https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601'>format ISO 8601</a>."

msgid ""
"The date this content was last modified, with an optional time value. "
"Needs to be in <a href='https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601'>ISO "
"8601</a> format. Can be the same as the 'Article modification date' "
"tag."
msgstr ""
"La data que aqueste contengut foguèt modificat per la darrièra còp, "
"amb una valor opcionala de temps. Deu èsser dins lo fòrmant <a "
"href='https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601'>ISO 8601</a>. pòt "
"èsser la meteissa que la balisa « Article modification date »."

msgid ""
"Preferred page location or URL to help eliminate duplicate content for "
"search engines, e.g., <em>https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0117500/</em>."
msgstr ""
"Emplaçament preferit de la pagina o URL per ajudar a eliminar lo "
"contengut duplicat pels motors de cèrcha, per exemple, "
"<em>https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0117500/</em>."

msgid "All meta tags in the \"@group\" group."
msgstr "Totes las balisas meta dins lo grope \"@group\"."

msgid ""
"Used to control whether a browser caches a specific page locally. Not "
"commonly used. Should be used in conjunction with the Pragma meta tag."
msgstr ""
"Utilizat per controlar se un navegador met a l’escòp una pagina "
"especifica en memòria locala. Pas comunament utilizat. Deuriá èsser "
"utilizat en conjuncion amb la meta etiqueta Pragma."

msgid "Used for paginated content by providing URL with rel='next' link."
msgstr ""
"Utilizat per contengut paginat en provesissent una URL amb un ligam "
"rel='next'."

msgid ""
"Used to control whether a browser caches a specific page locally. Not "
"commonly used. Should be used in conjunction with the Cache-Control "
"meta tag."
msgstr ""
"Utilizat per controlar se un navegador met una pagina especifica en "
"memòria locala. Pas plan utilizat. Deuriá èsser emplegat en "
"combinason amb la meta tag Cache-Control."

msgid "Used for paginated content by providing URL with rel='prev' link."
msgstr ""
"Utilizat per contengut paginat en fornissant una URL amb un ligam "
"rel='prev'."

msgid ""
"Provides the fifteen <a "
"href=\"https://dublincore.org/documents/dces/\">Dublin Core Metadata "
"Element Set 1.1</a> meta tags from the <a "
"href=\"https://dublincore.org/\">Dublin Core Metadata Institute</a>."
msgstr ""
"Prepausa los quinze meta-marquetas <a "
"href=\"https://dublincore.org/documents/dces/\">Dublin Core Metadata "
"Element Set 1.1</a> del <a href=\"https://dublincore.org/\">Institut "
"de Metadata Dublin Core</a>."

msgid ""
"Provides forty additional meta tags from the <a "
"href=\"https://dublincore.org/\">Dublin Core Metadata Institute</a>."
msgstr ""
"Provesís quaranta meta balisas suplementàrias del <a "
"href=\"https://dublincore.org/\">Dublin Core Metadata Institute</a>."

msgid "Metatag: Hreflang"
msgstr "Metatag: Hreflang"

msgid ""
"A semi-colon -separated string that must contain the 'polling-uri=' "
"value with the full URL to a <a "
"href='https://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/p/?LinkID=314019'>Badge Schema "
"XML file</a>. May also contain 'frequency=' value set to either 30, "
"60, 360, 720 or 1440 (default) which specifies (in minutes) how often "
"the URL should be polled."
msgstr ""
"Una cadena separada per un punt e virgula que deu contenir la valor "
"'polling-uri=' amb l’URL complèt d’un <a "
"href='https://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/p/?LinkID=314019'>fichièr XML "
"del esquema de Badja</a>. Pòt tanben conténer la valor 'frequency=' "
"definida sus 30, 60, 360, 720 o 1440 (per defaut), que precisa (en "
"minutas) la frequéncia amb que l’URL deu èsser interrogat."

msgid "Metatag: Page Manager"
msgstr "Metatag: Gestor de paginas"

msgid "If checked, the field will be placed in the sidebar on entity forms."
msgstr ""
"Se seleccionat, lo camp serà plaçat dins la barra laterala dels "
"formularis d’entitats."

msgid "Use sidebar: Yes"
msgstr "Utilizar la barra laterala: Òc"

msgid ""
"Control when the browser's internal cache of the current page should "
"expire. The date must to be an <a "
"href='https://www.csgnetwork.com/timerfc1123calc.html'>RFC-1123</a>-compliant "
"date string that is represented in Greenwich Mean Time (GMT), e.g. "
"'Thu, 01 Sep 2016 00:12:56 GMT'. Set to '0' to stop the page being "
"cached entirely."
msgstr ""
"Contraròtle quand lo còde intern del navegador per la pagina "
"correnta deu expirar. La data deu èsser una cadena de data <a "
"href='https://www.csgnetwork.com/timerfc1123calc.html'>conforma a "
"l'RFC-1123</a> e representada en ora mitjana de Greenwich (GMT), per "
"exemple 'Thu, 01 Sep 2016 00:12:56 GMT'. Ajustatz a '0' per empachar "
"que la pagina siá totalament picada en memòria."

msgid ""
"The number of seconds to wait before refreshing the page. May also "
"force redirect to another page using the format '5; "
"url=https://example.com/', which would be triggered after five "
"seconds."
msgstr ""
"Lo nombre de segondas d’esperar abans de renovar la pagina. pòt "
"tanben forçar una redireccion cap a una autra pagina en utilizant lo "
"fòrmulari '5; url=https://example.com/', que se deu activar après "
"cinc segondas."

msgid ""
"The secure URL to an audio file that complements this object. All "
"'http://' URLs will automatically be converted to 'https://'."
msgstr ""
"L'URL segura d'un fichièr audio que complementa aqueste objècte. "
"Totes los URL 'http://' seràn convertits automaticament en "
"'https://'."

msgid "Metatag Extended Permissions"
msgstr "Permissions estendudas de Metatag"

msgid "Access %tag in %group"
msgstr "Accedir a %tag dins %group"

msgid ""
"A color in hexadecimal format, e.g. '#0000ff' for blue; must include "
"the '#' symbol. Used by some browsers to control the background color "
"of the toolbar, the color used with an icon, etc."
msgstr ""
"Un color en format hexadecimal, per exemple '#0000ff' per lo blaus; "
"deu comprene lo simbòl '#'. Utilizat per qualques navegadors per "
"controlar la color de fons de la barra d'estrament, la color utilizada "
"amb una icòna, etc."

msgid ""
"The <a href='https://ogp.me/'>Open Graph meta tags</a> are used to "
"control how Facebook, Pinterest, LinkedIn and other social networking "
"sites interpret the site's content.<br><br>The Facebook <a "
"href='https://developers.facebook.com/tools/debug/'>Sharing "
"Debugger</a> lets you preview how your content will look when it's "
"shared to Facebook and debug any issues with your Open Graph tags."
msgstr ""
"Las <a href='https://ogp.me/'>balizas meta Open Graph</a> son "
"utilizadas per contraròtlar cossí Facebook, Pinterest, LinkedIn e "
"d'autras rets socialas interpreton lo contengut del siti.<br><br>Lo <a "
"href='https://developers.facebook.com/tools/debug/'>Sharing "
"Debugger</a> de Facebook vos permet de prévisualizar cossí vòstre "
"contengut se mostrarà quand es partejat sus Facebook e de detectar e "
"corregir los problèmas amb las vòstras balizas Open Graph."

msgid ""
"These <a href='https://ogp.me/'>Open Graph meta tags</a> are for "
"describing products.<br><br>The Facebook <a "
"href='https://developers.facebook.com/tools/debug/'>Sharing "
"Debugger</a> lets you preview how your content will look when it's "
"shared to Facebook and debug any issues with your Open Graph tags."
msgstr ""
"Aqueles <a href='https://ogp.me/'>metadatas Open Graph</a> son per "
"descriure de produches.<br><br>Lo <a "
"href='https://developers.facebook.com/tools/debug/'>Debugguer de "
"Partatge</a> de Facebook vos permet de previsualizar cossí vòstre "
"contengut va èsser vist quand es partejat sus Facebook e de depurar "
"qualsòm de problèmas amb vòstres metadatas Open Graph."

msgid ""
"The URL to a unique image representing the content of the page. Do not "
"use a generic image such as your website logo, author photo, or other "
"image that spans multiple pages. Images larger than 120x120px will be "
"resized and cropped square based on longest dimension. Images smaller "
"than 60x60px will not be shown. If the 'type' is set to Photo then the "
"image must be at least 280x150px."
msgstr ""
"L’URL cap a una imatge unica que representa lo contengut de la "
"pagina. Cap de utilizar una imatge generica coma lo logòteu del "
"vòstre siti, la fòto de l’autor, o d’autras imagess que "
"s’estendan sus mantunas paginas. Las imagess mai grandas qu’un "
"tamanh de 120x120px seràn redimensionadas e rogadas en quadrat segon "
"la dimension mai longa. Las imagess mai pichonas qu’un tamanh de "
"60x60px seràn pas afichadas. Se lo « type » es definit coma Photo, "
"la imatge deu èsser al mens 280x150px."

msgid ""
"The full URL for an MP4 video (h.264) or audio (AAC) stream, takes "
"precedence over the other media player field."
msgstr ""
"L’URL completa per un viech MP4 (h.264) o un flux d’audi (AAC) ten "
"la precedença sus l’autre camp del lecteur multimèdia."

msgid ""
"To use tokens to image fields, the image field on that entity bundle "
"(content type, term, etc) must have the \"Token\" display settings "
"enabled, the image field must not be hidden, and it must be set to "
"output as an image, e.g. using the \"Thumbnail\" field formatter. It "
"is also recommended to use an appropriate image style that resizes the "
"image rather than output the original image; see individual meta tag "
"descriptions for size recommendations."
msgstr ""
"Utilizar de tokens pels camps d'imatge, lo camp d'imatge sus aquel "
"grop d'entitats (tipa de contengut, tèrme, etc.) deu aver activat las "
"configuracions d'afichatge \"Token\", lo camp d'imatge deu pas èsser "
"escondut, e deu èsser configurat per tornar sortir coma una imatge, "
"per exemple en utilizant lo formatador de camp \"Miniatura\". Es "
"tanben recomandat d'utilizar un estil d'imatge adapat que redimensiona "
"l'imatge en luòc de tornar sortir l'imatge originala; vei las "
"descripcion individualas dels meta tags per las recomendaciones de "
"talha."

msgid ""
"This will be able to extract the URL from an image field if the field "
"is configured properly."
msgstr ""
"Aquò serà capable d'estrachar l'URL d'un camp d'imatge se lo camp es "
"configurat corrèctament."

msgid ""
"Used to rate content for audience appropriateness. This tag has little "
"known influence on search engine rankings, but can be used by "
"browsers, browser extensions, and apps. The <a "
"href='https://www.metatags.org/meta_name_rating'>most common "
"options</a> are general, mature, restricted, 14 years, safe for kids. "
"If you follow the <a "
"href='https://www.rtalabel.org/index.php?content=howto'>RTA "
"Documentation</a> you should enter RTA-5042-1996-1400-1577-RTA"
msgstr ""
"Utilizat per calificar lo contengut segon son adreiça al public. "
"Aquesta etiqueta a pas gaire d’influéncia coneguda sus lo "
"rangiament dins los motors de recèrca, mas pòt èsser utilizada per "
"navigadors, extenssions de navigadors e aplicacions. Las <a "
"href='https://www.metatags.org/meta_name_rating'>opcions mai "
"comunas</a> son general, adult, restrench, 14 ans, segure per los "
"dròlles. Se seguissètz la <a "
"href='https://www.rtalabel.org/index.php?content=howto'>documentacion "
"RTA</a> cal inserir RTA-5042-1996-1400-1577-RTA"

msgid "@label of @type"
msgstr "@etiqueta de @tipus"

msgid "@label of @type @entity-type-label"
msgstr "@label de @type @entity-type-label"

msgid "This plugin will be cloned from these settings for each custom tag."
msgstr ""
"Aqueste plugin serà duplicat a partir d'aquestas configuracions per "
"cada etiqueta personalizada."

msgid "Place field in collapsed details container"
msgstr "Plaçar lo camp dins lo contenidor de detalhs plegats"

msgid "Trim method for trimmable tags."
msgstr "Metòde trim pels gèstes qu’an a èsser taillats."

msgid "Tag-specific maximum length"
msgstr "Longor màxima especificala per etiqueta"

msgid "Tag maximum length in characters"
msgstr "Longor maxima de la balisa en caractèrs"

msgid ""
"Adds individual permissions for each meta tag, allowing for "
"fine-grained access to the meta tags. Note: this may lead to "
"performance issues on the permissions admin page, please see the "
"included README.txt file for details."
msgstr ""
"Ajusta de permissios individualas per cada meta etiqueta, permetent un "
"accès finament detalhat a las meta etiquetas. Remarca: aquò pòt "
"menar a de problèmas de rendiment sus la pagina d'administracion dels "
"permissos, mercé de consultar lo fichièr README.txt inclus per mai "
"de detalhs."

msgid "Mask icon color"
msgstr "Color de l'icòna del masca"

msgid ""
"Color attribute for SVG (mask) icon in hexadecimal format, e.g. "
"'#0000ff'. Setting it will break HTML validation. If not set macOS "
"Safari ignores the Mask Icon entirely, making the Icon: SVG completely "
"useless."
msgstr ""
"Atribut de color per l'icòna SVG (mask) en format hexadecimal, per "
"exemple '#0000ff'. La configuracion d'aquesta valor rompra la "
"validacion HTML. Se ne es pas configurat, macOS Safari ignorarà "
"totalament l'icòna Mask, çò que fasiá l'icòna SVG completament "
"inutila."

msgid "Mask icon (SVG)"
msgstr "Icòna de masca (SVG)"

msgid "Open Graph Product: Price availability"
msgstr "Open Graph Producte: Disponibilitat del prètz"

msgid "Open Graph Product: Product condition"
msgstr "Open Graph Produit: Estat del produit"

msgid "Open Graph Product: Retailer Item ID"
msgstr "Open Graph Producte : ID d'item del torista"

msgid "Product condition"
msgstr "Condicion del produch"

msgid "The condition of the product."
msgstr "L'estat del produch."

msgid "Retailer Item ID"
msgstr "Identificant d'element de revendaire"

msgid "The ID of the product as provided by the retailer."
msgstr "L’identificant del produsit tal coma fornit pel comèrciant."

msgid ""
"Empty update script to clear the site's caches so the new token "
"replacement functionality will work."
msgstr ""
"Script de mesa a jorn void per netejar las caissas del sit per que la "
"nòva foncionalitat de remplacament de tòkens foncione."

msgid "Metatag Trimming Options"
msgstr "Opcions de reduccion dels metatags"

msgid ""
"Many Meta-Tags can be trimmed on a specific length for search engine "
"optimization.<br/>If the value is set to '0' or left empty, the whole "
"Metatag will be untrimmed."
msgstr ""
"Dins mantuns Meta-Labels, se pòt talhar a una longor especifica per "
"l’optimizacion pels moturs de recèrca.<br/>Se lo valor es definit "
"coma '0' o demorat void, tot lo Meta-Label serà pas talhat."

msgid "Meta Tags:"
msgstr "Meta Balises:"

msgid "Trim the Meta Tag after the word on the given value"
msgstr "Eliminez la Meta Etiqueta après lo mot sus la valor donada"

msgid "Trim the Meta Tag on the given value"
msgstr "Redusir la etiqueta Meta sus la valor donada"

msgid "Trim the Meta Tag before the word on the given value"
msgstr "Escurcir lo Meta Tag abans lo mot sul valor donat"

msgid "Wrap the meta tags in a collapsed details container."
msgstr "Enrotla las balisas meta dins un conteneire de detalhs plegats."

msgid ""
"If checked, the contents of the field will be placed inside a "
"collapsed details container."
msgstr ""
"Se controlat, los contenguts del camp seràn placats a l'interior d'un "
"conteneire de detalhs plegat."

msgid "Use details container: Yes"
msgstr "Utilizar lo containèr de detals : Òc"

msgid "Use details container: No"
msgstr "Utilizar lo contenir de detalhs : Non"

msgid ""
"Geo-spatial information in 'latitude; longitude' format, e.g. "
"'50.167958; -97.133185'; <a "
"href='https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Geographic_coordinate_system' "
"aria-label='see Wikipedia for details on the geographic coordinate "
"system'>see Wikipedia for details</a>."
msgstr ""
"Informacion geo-espacial en format 'latitud; longitud', per exemple "
"'50.167958; -97.133185'; <a "
"href='https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Geographic_coordinate_system' "
"aria-label='voir Wikipedia per mai de detalhs sus lo sistèma de "
"coordonadas geograficas'>veire Wikipedia per mai de detalhs</a>."

msgid ""
"Geo-spatial information in 'latitude, longitude' format, e.g. "
"'50.167958, -97.133185'; <a "
"href='https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ICBM_address' aria-label='see "
"Wikipedia for details on ICBM addresses'>see Wikipedia for "
"details</a>."
msgstr ""
"Informacions geo-espacialas en format 'latitud, longitud', per exemple "
"'50.167958, -97.133185'; <a "
"href='https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ICBM_address' aria-label='see "
"Wikipedia for details on ICBM addresses'>vejatz Wikipedia per mai de "
"detalhs</a>."

msgid "Token Or"
msgstr "Token Or"

msgid "Add max height value"
msgstr "Apondre una valor de naut maximum"

msgid "Metatag Custom Routes (Paths)"
msgstr "Rutes Personalizadas de Metatag (Camins)"

msgid "Route / Path"
msgstr "Ruta / Camí"

msgid ""
"Enter the route (path) for this new configuration, starting with a "
"leading slash.<br />Note: this must already exist as a path in Drupal."
msgstr ""
"Entratz lo camin (rota) per aquesta novèla configuracion, començant "
"per una barra iniciala.<br />Nota : aquò deu ja existir coma un camin "
"dins Drupal."

msgid "Site validation: SIWECOS"
msgstr "Validacion del site: SIWECOS"

msgid "Google Site Verification"
msgstr "Verificacion de sit Google"

msgid "SIWECOS"
msgstr "SIWECOS"

msgid "Metatag widget options"
msgstr "Opcions del giny Metatag"

msgid ""
"Various options for the field widget used on entity forms, e.g. on "
"content type forms."
msgstr ""
"Diferentas opcions pels widgets de camps utilizats sus las formas "
"d’entitats, per exemple sus las formas de tipe de contengut."

msgid "Scroll maximum height"
msgstr "Desplaçament al naut maxim"

msgid "eg 500px or 8rem"
msgstr "ex. 500px o 8rem"

msgid ""
"To enable scrolling please enter a value and its units, e.g. 500px, "
"8rem, etc. Removing this value will remove the scroll."
msgstr ""
"Per activar lo desplaçament, mercés d'entrar una valor e sas "
"unitats, p.e. 500px, 8rem, etc. Suprimir aquesta valor suprimirà lo "
"desplaçament."

msgid "Define the author of a page."
msgstr "Definís l'autor d'una pagina."

msgid ""
"The <a href=\"@module\">Token OR module</a> is suggested for when the "
"basic content tokens are not flexible enough, e.g. to make a meta tag "
"show the contents of one field if it is filled in or another if the "
"first one is empty."
msgstr ""
"Lo <a href=\"@module\">Token O modòl</a> es suggerit quand los tokens "
"de contengut basics son pas assez flexibles, per exemple per far "
"aparéisser dins una meta etiqueta lo contengut d’un camp se es "
"emplenat o d’un autre se lo primièr es void."

msgid "Href per language"
msgstr "Href per lenga"

msgid ""
"This was expected to be an array but it is not: \n"
"%value"
msgstr ""
"Se pensava que aquò seriá una lista mas o es pas: \n"
"%value"

msgid ""
"This could not be unserialized: \n"
"%value"
msgstr ""
"Aqueste podiá pas èsser deserializat :  \n"
"%value"

msgid "Metatag Field Diff"
msgstr "Diferéncia del camp Metatag"

msgid "Use Maxlength module to force these limits?"
msgstr "Utilizatz lo mòdule Maxlength per forçar aquestes limits?"

msgid "Install the Maxlength module to enable this option."
msgstr "Installatz lo module Maxlength per activar aquesta opcional."

msgid "Intended workflow"
msgstr "Flux de trabalh previst"

msgid ""
"Allows assigning meta tags to be used on custom routes, equivalent to "
"custom paths."
msgstr ""
"Permet d'assignar de meta etiquetas per èsser utilizadas sus de rotas "
"personalizadas, equivalents als camins personalizats."

msgid ""
"Indicate to search engines and other page scrapers whether or not "
"links should be followed. See <a "
"href='https://w3c.github.io/webappsec/specs/referrer-policy/'>the W3C "
"specifications</a> for further details. Note: this serves the same "
"purpose as the HTTP header by the same name."
msgstr ""
"Indica a las machetas de recèrca e a d'autres aspiradors de paginas "
"se los ligams devon èsser seguits o non. Vejatz <a "
"href='https://w3c.github.io/webappsec/specs/referrer-policy/'>las "
"especificacions del W3C</a> per mai de detalhs. Notar: aquò servís "
"al meteis escòp que l'encabrament HTTP que pòt portar lo meteis nom."

msgid "Max Snippet"
msgstr "Màger Extrait"

msgid ""
"Use a number character as a textual snippet for this search result. "
"\"0\" equals \"nosnippet\". \"-1\" will let the search engine decide "
"the most effective length."
msgstr ""
"Utilizatz un caractèr numeric coma un extrach textual per aqueste "
"resultat de recèrca. \"0\" voliá dire \"pas d’extrach\". \"-1\" "
"daissarà al motor de recèrca la decision de la longor mai eficaça."

msgid ""
"Use a maximum of number seconds as a video snippet for videos on this "
"page in search results. \"0\" will use a static a image. \"-1\" means "
"there is no limit."
msgstr ""
"Utilizatz un maximun de nombre de segondas coma un extrach de vidèo "
"per las vidèos d'aquesta pagina dins los resultats de recèrca. «0» "
"utilizara una imatge estada. «-1» vòl dire que i a pas de limita."

msgid "Max Image Preview"
msgstr "Previsualizacion maxima de l'imatge"

msgid "Unavailable after date"
msgstr "Inaccessible après la data"

msgid "Do not show this page in search results after the specified date"
msgstr ""
"Non mòstrar aquesta pagina dins los resultats de recèrca aprèp la "
"data especificada"

msgid ""
"There were no overridden Metatag records that needed to be updated to "
"store the data using JSON."
msgstr ""
"I foguèt pas de registres Metatag susescriches que calguèsse metre a "
"jorn per estocar las donadas en utilizant JSON."

msgid ""
"Processed @processed of @total updating Metatag records with the "
"Publisher or Name meta tags."
msgstr ""
"Processat @processed de @total en actualizant los registres Metatag "
"amb las balisas meta Publisher o Name."

msgid "There were no Metatag records to update."
msgstr "I a pas agut de registres Metatag per metre a jorn."

msgid "Removed meta tags from the @config Metatag configuration."
msgstr "Metatags enleigidas de la configuracion Metatag @config."

msgid "Metatag: Google Plus is not enabled, nothing to do."
msgstr "Metatag: Google Plus es pas activat, res a far."

msgid "Metatag: Google Plus has been uninstalled."
msgstr "Metatag : Google Plus a estat desinstallat."

msgid ""
"Corrected the Twitter Card \"type\" value in the @config Metatag "
"configuration."
msgstr ""
"Corrigit la valor \"type\" de la carta Twitter dins la configuracion "
"@config Metatag."

msgid "The computed meta tags for the entity."
msgstr "Las balisas meta calculadas per l'entitat."

msgid "Deprecated module, do not use. Will be removed in 3.0.0."
msgstr "Modul obsolet, a pas utilizar. Serà remogat dins la version 3.0.0."

msgid ""
"Notes:<ul><li>no other fields are required for a Summary "
"card</li><li>Media player card requires the 'title', 'description', "
"'media player URL', 'media player width', 'media player height' and "
"'image' fields,</li><li>Summary Card with Large Image card requires "
"the 'Summary' field and the 'image' field,</li><li>App Card requires "
"the 'iPhone app ID' field, the 'iPad app ID' field and the 'Google "
"Play app ID' field,</li></ul>"
msgstr ""
"Notas:<ul><li>cap autres camps son requerits pel fichièr de "
"resumit</li><li>la carta de lectors de mitan requisís los camps "
"'títol', 'descricion', 'URL del lector de mitan', 'largor del lector "
"de mitan', 'autor del lector de mitan' e 'imatge',</li><li>la carta de "
"resumit amb una imatge granda requerís los camps 'Resumit' e "
"'imatge',</li><li>la carta d’aplicacion necessita los camps "
"'identificant de l’aplicacion iPhone', 'identificant de "
"l’aplicacion iPad' e 'identificant de l’aplicacion Google "
"Play',</li></ul>"

msgid "Separator used with multiple values"
msgstr "Separador utilizat amb de valors multiples"

msgid ""
"Controls the separator used when a meta tag allows multiple values. "
"Multiple characters can be used together, it does not have to be one "
"single character long. Defaults to \":default\"."
msgstr ""
"Contròla lo separatòr utilizat quand una meta etiqueta permet "
"mantuns valors. Mantuns caractèrs pòdon èsser utilizats ensems, "
"pòt pas èsser sonque un sol caractèr. Per defaut, es \":default\"."

msgid ""
"Multiple values may be used, separated by `:delimiter`. Note: Tokens "
"that return multiple values will be handled automatically."
msgstr ""
"Diverses valors pòdon èsser utilizadas, separadas per `:delimiter`. "
"Nota: Los tokens que retornan de valors multiples seràn gestionats "
"automaticament."

msgid ""
"The full URL for loading a media player, specifically an iframe for an "
"embedded video rather than the URL to a page that contains a player. "
"Required when using the Player Card type."
msgstr ""
"L’URL completa per cargar un lecteur multimèdia, especificament un "
"iframe per una vidèo incorporada e non pas l’URL d’una pagina "
"contenent un lecteur. Es necessari quand s’utiliza lo tipe Player "
"Card."

msgid ""
"The height of the media player iframe, in pixels. Required when using "
"the Player Card type."
msgstr ""
"L'alçada de l'iframe del lectors multimedia, en pixeus. Requirit "
"quand s'utiliza lo tipe Player Card."

msgid ""
"The width of the media player iframe, in pixels. Required when using "
"the Player Card type."
msgstr ""
"La largor de l'iframe del lector de mèdia, en pixels. Requirit quand "
"se utiliza lo tipe Carta del Lector."

msgid ""
"This will be truncated to a maximum of %max characters after any "
"tokens are processed."
msgstr ""
"Aquesta serà truncada a un maxim de %max caractèrs après que totas "
"las tokens sián procesadas."

msgid ""
"Because of how tokens are processed in meta tags, use of the Maxlength "
"module may not provide an accurate representation of the actual "
"current length of each meta tag, so it may cause more problem than it "
"is worth."
msgstr ""
"A causa de la manièra que los tokens son tractats dins las meta "
"balizas, l'usatge del modulus Maxlength pòt pas fornir una "
"representacion precisa de la longitud actuala de caduna meta baliza, e "
"doncas pòt causar mai de problèmas que çò que ne val la pena."

msgid ""
"Control the Metatag settings pages. Does not control access to the "
"Metatag field on content forms, etc, use the Field Permissions module "
"or hook_form_alter()."
msgstr ""
"Controlatz las paginas de las configuracions de Metatag. Contraròtla "
"pas l'accès al camp Metatag dins los formularis de contengut, etc., "
"utilizatz lo module Field Permissions o hook_form_alter()."

msgid "End of the word trimming"
msgstr "Fin de la troncadura de mots"

msgid "This module provides support to define and manage custom meta tags."
msgstr ""
"Aqueste modulus provesís un sosten per definir e gerir d'etiquetas "
"meta personalizadas."

msgid ""
"The module provides the option to create different <a "
"href=\":metatag_custom_tag\">\"Custom Tags\"</a> to use for different "
"purposes."
msgstr ""
"Lo module provesís l’opcion de crear diferentas <a "
"href=\":metatag_custom_tag\">\"Etiquetas Personalizadas\"</a> per "
"èsser utilizadas per de malhumes diferents."

msgid "The best way of using Metatag: Custom Tags is as follows:"
msgstr "La melhora manièra d'utilizar Metatag: Custom Tags es la seguenta:"

msgid ""
"Create the <a href=\":metatag_custom_tag_create\">\"Custom Tag\"</a>, "
"fill in the specific values that every page should have."
msgstr ""
"Crea lo <a href=\":metatag_custom_tag_create\">« Etiqueta "
"Personnalizada »</a>, emplena las valors especificas que cada pagina "
"deu aver."

msgid "Configure Custom tags below."
msgstr "Configuratz las balisas personalizadas çaijós."

msgid "Metatag: Custom Tags"
msgstr "Metatag: Etiquetas Personalizadas"

msgid "Provides support to define and manage custom meta tags."
msgstr ""
"Proporciona supòrt per definir e gerir de balisas meta "
"personalizadas."

msgid "Add Custom tag"
msgstr "Apondre una etiqueta personalizabla"

msgid "Administer Custom tags"
msgstr "Administrar etiquetas personalizadas"

msgid "Control the main settings pages and modify custom tags."
msgstr ""
"Contròla las paginas principalas de configuracion e modifica las "
"esclòpas personalizadas."

msgid "Delete Custom tag"
msgstr "Supprimir l’etiqueta personalizada"

msgid "Specify the name of the custom tag."
msgstr "Especificatz lo nom del marcador personalizat."

msgid "Specify the description of the Custom tag."
msgstr "Especificar la descripcion de l’etiqueta Personalizada."

msgid "Select the HTML element of the Custom tag."
msgstr "Seleccionatz l'element HTML de l’etiqueta personalizaa."

msgid "Value attribute"
msgstr "Atribut de valor"

